%% Models as a Service - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>(Kuadrant)
    participant Limitador as Limitador<br/>(Kuadrant)
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant KubeAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KServe as Model Backend<br/>(KServe)

    Note over Client,KServe: Flow 1: Token Issuance

    Client->>Gateway: POST /maas-api/v1/tokens<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OpenShift user token)
    Gateway->>Authorino: Validate request
    Authorino->>KubeAPI: TokenReview (validate user token)
    KubeAPI-->>Authorino: Token valid + user identity
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: GET /v1/tiers/lookup<br/>(tier metadata enrichment)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Tier: premium
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/tokens<br/>(validated, prefix-stripped)
    MaaSAPI->>KubeAPI: TokenReview (re-validate)
    MaaSAPI->>KubeAPI: Create Namespace (if needed)
    MaaSAPI->>KubeAPI: Create ServiceAccount
    MaaSAPI->>KubeAPI: CreateToken (short-lived SA token)
    KubeAPI-->>MaaSAPI: SA Token issued
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: Response: {token, expiry}
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response with SA token

    Note over Client,KServe: Flow 2: Model Inference (auth + rate limiting)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{namespace}/{llm-name}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA token)
    Gateway->>Authorino: Validate request
    Authorino->>KubeAPI: TokenReview (validate SA token)
    KubeAPI-->>Authorino: Token valid + SA identity
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/tiers/lookup<br/>(resolve user tier)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Tier: premium
    Authorino->>KubeAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(check llminferenceservices:post)
    KubeAPI-->>Authorino: Authorized
    Gateway->>Limitador: Rate limit check<br/>(20 req/2m, 50k tokens/1m)
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Allowed
    Gateway->>KServe: Forward inference request<br/>(with identity headers)
    KServe-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,KServe: Flow 3: Model Discovery

    Client->>Gateway: GET /v1/models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>Authorino: Validate request
    Authorino->>KubeAPI: TokenReview
    KubeAPI-->>Authorino: Valid
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: GET /v1/models
    MaaSAPI->>KubeAPI: List LLMInferenceServices<br/>(all namespaces)
    KubeAPI-->>MaaSAPI: LLMInferenceService list
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: OpenAI-compatible model list
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response
